  "prompt": "What is a diamond?",
  "response": "A diamond is a precious gemstone that is formed from carbon atoms arranged in a crystal structure known as a diamond lattice. This unique arrangement gives diamonds their remarkable hardness and brilliance. Diamonds are typically found in igneous rocks known as kimberlite and can also be created synthetically in laboratories.\n\nDiamonds are graded based on the \"Four Cs\": carat weight, cut, color, and clarity. These factors influence their quality, appearance, and value. In addition to being used in jewelry, diamonds also have industrial applications due to their hardness, including in cutting, grinding, and drilling tools. Diamonds are often associated with luxury, love, and commitment, especially in engagement rings and wedding bands.",
